CYCLOSPORA - USA/CANADA
=======================
See Also
Cyclospora & strawberries - Texas, USA get promed archive.960617
For references get promed-1995 Cyclospora
Source: Boston Globe newspaper, Sat.22 June 1996. p.17

Massachusetts
-------------
18/22 women attending a bridal lunch party in Cape Cod in June fell ill one
week later (including the bride, honeymooning in Spain). Symptoms were
severe diarrhea, leading to weight loss of up to 30lbs, and hospitalization
for fluid replacement in one case. In one case, the only food reportedly
eaten was a fruit salad containing strawberries and other berries.
Mass. Dept of Public Health said this outbreak brings the case count for the
state to 92, with 36 confirmed by laboratory tests.
USA/Canada
----------
CDC reports 300-400 cases in several states and Canada in recent weeks. The
disease is rarely fatal, but dangerous for people with damaged immune
systems. It is treatable with sulfabased drugs.
